summary: This is an email chain from January 2020 regarding the status of bank records subpoenaed from USAA for Ghislaine Maxwell's criminal case. It shows coordination between legal staff about receiving and distributing the records, including delivery to the SDNY.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The email chain is about the status of subpoenaed bank records from USAA for her criminal case.

events.title: USAA records request notification
events.description: An automated notification is sent indicating a request for bank records for Ghislaine Maxwell has been received and is being prepared.

events.title: Coordination on received Maxwell bank records
events.description: Legal staff correspond about having received the subpoenaed USAA bank records for Ghislaine Maxwell and confirm a copy was delivered to the SDNY the prior week.

keyFacts: Bank records for Ghislaine Maxwell were subpoenaed from USAA as part of the criminal investigation.
The records request was processed with a specific invoice (#40659875) and claim number (#40897182).
A copy of the received USAA bank records was delivered to the Southern District of New York (SDNY) prosecutors in late December 2019 or early January 2020.
The email chain shows internal legal team coordination regarding the receipt and distribution of discovery materials in Maxwell's case.
